<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="2fb5685f-e854-5999-ba0d-409b48da3b3f" activityNameId="8a4da58b-9609-4ac8-8bb4-940e5482c3ae" parentActivityId="4c382d79-bee5-57e5-aca5-f2289c97a223" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">chlorine dioxide production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Chloryl radical</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Chlorine peroxide</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Chlorine(IV) oxide</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Doxcide 50</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Anthium dioxcide</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of 1 kg of chlorine dioxide. The dataset includes the processing of the raw materials and chemicals used for production. It also includes estimated emissions to air and water from production (incomplete), as well as estimated energy demand and infrastructure of the plant (approximation). Solid wastes are omitted.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of chlorine dioxide by the R2 process. Chlorine dioxide is a gas of yellowish-green to orange colour. This substance has an irritant, pungent odour, similar to a mixture of chlorine and ozone. High concentrations of its gas are very explosive. Chlorine dioxide is furthermore easily soluble in water – but it is at the same time also a very unstable gas that easily decomposes into chlorine and oxygen (Vogt et al. 2010).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Chlorine gas is the most widely used bleaching agent, especially for high quality cellulose.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">This dataset is based on literature data and stoechiometric calculations, as well as approximations based on data from a large chemical factory (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings &amp; Graphical Papers. ecoinvent report No. 11. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Vogt, H., Balej, J., Bennett, J. E., Wintzer, P., Sheikh, S. A., Gallone, P., Vasudevan, S. and Pelin, K. 2010. Chlorine Oxides and Chlorine Oxygen Acids. Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data used has no specific geographical origin as it is based on stoechiometric calculations and estimations. It is assumed to be representative of the production processes in this geography. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Production from sodium chlorate and chloride by R2 process with a process yield of 95%. The inventory is based on stoechiometric calculations. The emissions to air (0.2 wt% of raw material input) and water were estimated using mass balance. Treatment of the waste water in a internal waste water treatment plant was assumed (elimination efficiency of 90% for C).</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data in this dataset come from different years, but overall form the most realistic picture of the production. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
